  "description":[
    "The mission of the Boston Residents Jobs Policy is to increase the employment opportunities for Boston&rsquo;s residents, minorities, and women. The Boston Residents Jobs Ordinance sets goals on construction-related projects funded by or approved by the City. The ordinance stated goals aim to have 51% of the work hours performed by Boston residents, 40% by people of color, and 12% by women on a trade-by-trade basis."
